cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a deep learning architecture for stereo regression, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of 3-D convolutions, which are commonly used in deep learning for image and video processing, and the soft argmin operation, which is a differentiable optimization technique. These techniques are related to ML subfields such as deep learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these categories are also likely to be relevant.
